Package: santree
Title: Creates Sankey Diagrams from Phylogenetic Trees
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(person("Brian", "O'Meara", email = "omeara.brian@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre")), person("Jodie", "Wiggins", role = c("aut")))
Description: Sankey diagrams are a way of showing flow between nodes. This allows this, but for phylogenetic trees (networks to come later). The advantage of this is beautiful flowing lines as well as showing how diversity separates at nodes.
Depends: R (>= 3.5.1)
License: GPL (>= 2)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Requires:
    ape
    phangorn
    riverplot
    phytools
Suggests:
    testthat
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
